# Import Path Hygiene

- When adding or editing imports, check whether an import path can be shortened while staying consistent with existing project patterns.
- Prefer the shorter existing path when the same symbol is already re-exported from a nearby `index.ts` or other established barrel file.
- Prefer concise relative imports when the file is in the same feature area and a shorter local path is already used nearby.
- Do not create new barrel files or perform broad import rewrites just to shorten paths unless the task explicitly asks for that refactor.
- If a linter or IDE warning says `Import can be shortened`, treat it as a cleanup check before finishing the change.
